other_tests.findings: Fluid-filled, tubular blind-ending structure measuring up to 11 mm in diameter with adjacent fat stranding and thickening of the lateral conal fascia, consistent with acute appendicitis. No evidence of periappendiceal abscess or appendiceal rupture. Scattered streaky opacities at the lung bases compatible with subsegmental atelectasis. Normal findings in other abdominal and pelvic organs.
